															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tl333s" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1304786); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1304786&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250584" alt="TL333s" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1304786)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tl333s" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1304786); return false;" >TL333s</a></span> <span class="odate time_1416419541 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">19 Nov 2014 17:52</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2161367">
									

<p>We all know the story: innocent, normal people get swept up into an anomaly and are changed for life because of it. But need that change always be terrible and horrific? Lately, I've been feeling like something is missing from this site. This is an attempt to get that something back, that initial sense of wonder at the universe that drew me into the Foundation community.</p>
<p>Thanks for feedback goes to Dr. Reach, Soulless Singularity, TwistedGears and MaskedFerret (not on this site).</p>
<p>And yes, that's <a href="/scp-1795">SCP-1795</a> in there. I took some liberties with their behavior because, hey, how can we possibly know everything about a giant interstellar construct that isn't even anywhere near us? Everything else is original, or at least I made it up myself.</p>

							</div>

								
